## Implementation Plan

### Problem
`getsentry/codecov-action@main` has `enable-tests: true` by default, which
searches for JUnit XML files matching `**/*.junit.xml`. Since the project
produced no JUnit output, it emitted 3 warnings on every CI run:
- "No files found matching pattern: **/*.junit.xml"
- "No JUnit XML files found matching pattern: **/*.junit.xml"
- "Please ensure your test framework is generating JUnit XML output."

### Solution
Bun's test runner natively supports JUnit XML output via `bunfig.toml`.
Enabling it gives the codecov action something to find and unlocks test result
reporting (test counts, pass rate, test deltas vs base branch) for free.

### Changes
- `bunfig.toml`: added `[test.reporter]` section with `junit = "test-results.junit.xml"`
- `.gitignore`: added `*.junit.xml` under the test artifacts section so the
  generated file is not accidentally committed from local runs

No CI workflow changes needed — the codecov action's default glob
`**/*.junit.xml` already matches the output path.
